taken in the common way. I long regretted bitterly and still regret that I
had not given it to him by Inoculation. This I mention for the Sake of
Parents who omit that Operation on the Supposition that they should never
forgive themselves if a Child died under it; my Example showing that the
Regret may be the same either way, and that therefore the safer should be
chosen.
