Science is the only news. When you scan through a newspaper or magazine,
all the human interest stuff is the same old he-said-she-said, the politics
and economics the same sorry cyclic dramas, the fashions a pathetic
illusion of newness, and even the technology is predictable if you know the
science. Human nature doesn’t change much; science does, and the change
accrues, altering the world irreversibly.
        -- Stewart Brand, Whole Earth Discipline (2009), p 216
