I'm writing a book on magic, I explain, and I'm asked, Real magic? By real
magic people mean miracles, thaumaturgical acts, and supernatural powers.
No, I answer. Conjuring tricks, not real magic.
  
  Real magic, in other words, refers to the magic that is not real, while
the magic that is real, that can actually be done, is not real magic.
        -- from Net of Magic, by Lee Siegel
