%
There is an unfortunate optical illusion - a variant on the Doppler effect
- that besets all frauds. It's unfortunate, because it has the effect of
exacerbating the pecuniary losses that fraud victims endure, by unfairly
leaving them, like many rape victims, irrationally ashamed of themselves.
  
  The Doppler principle we posit holds that as a victim approaches a
swindler, he sees nothing but green lights. But as soon as he realizes that
his money is gone, he spins around and beholds, as if by magic, bright red
flags as far as the eye can see.
        -- Roger Parloff, senior editor, "More brazen than Madoff?",
Fortune, 20090331
