It is quite easy to show, decision-theoretically, that the greatest chance
of survival generally belongs to those who have most of their beliefs about
things which affect our survival ability true. Philosophy, however, is
totally irrelevant to survival from an evolutionary point of view. Natural
selection has no way of weeding out veridical intuitions about the basic
constitution of matter, for instance, from false ones, because humans have
not generally been killed before they can procreate due to having erroneous
metaphysical intuitions. Or bluntly put: having a true metaphysical theory
does not help you getting laid.
        -- Staffan Angere
